           <p3>Part of A SIMPLY FABOULOUS THANKSGIVING</p3>
        <div id="Focaccia">
          <h1> Focaccia with caramelized Onions,<br>Cranberries and Brie</h1>
           <p>Wow your taste buds with this festive focaccia appetizer topped with sweet caramelized onions, tart <br>
            cranberries, and creamie brie. It will become your new favorite holiday starter!</p>
        </div>
        <div>
           <img src="assets/focacca.png" alt="foto focaccia" />
         </div>
        <h5>Image: Sally Vegas</h5>
        </main>
        <div id="corpo">
            <span>FEATURED IN:</span>
            <div>
            <a href="Fresh Cranberry Recipes That Go Beyond Sause">Fresh Cranberry Recipes That Go Beyond Sause</a>
            </div>  
         <div>  
            <h2>Ingredients</h2>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h4>For the Focaccia:</h4>
                <ul>
                <li>4 cups (500gr) all-purpose flour</li>
                <li>1 1/2 teaspoon instant yeast</li>
                <li>1 1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
                <li>1 3/4 cups (350gr) lukewarm water</li>
                <li>1/4 cup extra vergine olive oil</li>
                </ul>
                <h4>For the Topping:</h4>
                <ul>
                <li>3 medium yellow onion, thinly sliced</li>
                <li>1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar</li>
                <li>1-2 olive oil, for brushing on top</li>
                <li>10 ounces brie, cut into cubes (scrape rind off with a paring knife <br>if desired, though it's not necessary)</li>
                <li>1 1/2 cup fresh or frozen cranberries</li>
             </ul>
             <h2>Method</h2>
            </div>
         <section>
             <h4>1. Make the Focaccia dough</h4>
              <p>In a medium size mixing bowl, or in a stand mixer with a paddle attachment,  mix togheter all<br>
                the dough ingredients until the flour is fully absorbed.  You don't need actually knead the<br>
                dough, thought I sometimes knead it a few times in  the bowl when  mixing by hand to incorporate<br>
                the last of the flour...
               </p>
         </section>
        </div>
